  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.1,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "- [David] The power, Wordsmiths,"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.3,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "the power."
      },
      {
        "start": 4.0,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "The words we're gonna take apart"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.8,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "with our bare hands today\nare dynamic and durable."
      },
      {
        "start": 9.8,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "So, I'll define the words,"
      },
      {
        "start": 11.1,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "I'll break them into their word parts,"
      },
      {
        "start": 13.0,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "and name some related words,"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.5,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "and then I'll use them in sentences."
      },
      {
        "start": 17.4,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Let's start with dynamic."
      },
      {
        "start": 19.0,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "It's an adjective, it\nmeans active and energetic."
      },
      {
        "start": 21.8,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "Which we could say about a person,"
      },
      {
        "start": 23.6,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "but it also means constantly changing,"
      },
      {
        "start": 25.7,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "which is less frequently\napplied to people."
      },
      {
        "start": 28.3,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "Durable is also an adjective,"
      },
      {
        "start": 30.2,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "and it means strong or long-lasting."
      },
      {
        "start": 32.8,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "A durable thing is tough and sturdy."
      },
      {
        "start": 36.1,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "I love both of these words so much."
      },
      {
        "start": 38.7,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "Let's talk about their origins."
      },
      {
        "start": 40.8,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Dynamic comes from the\nGreek word dynamikos,"
      },
      {
        "start": 44.1,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "meaning powerful, the\nroot dyn means power."
      },
      {
        "start": 48.1,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "The 17th and 18th century mathematician,"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.9,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz,\nwas the first person"
      },
      {
        "start": 53.8,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "to use dynamic in physics\nto describe powerful forces."
      },
      {
        "start": 57.9,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "Leibniz is cool."
      },
      {
        "start": 58.7,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "Maybe you've heard of Sir Isaac Newton,"
      },
      {
        "start": 61.0,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "the apple to the head gravity\nguy from England, yeah."
      },
      {
        "start": 64.4,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "Leibniz was like his math arch enemy."
      },
      {
        "start": 67.3,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "They discovered calculus,"
      },
      {
        "start": 68.5,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "which is a type of math at the same time."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.0,
        "duration": 1.0,
        "text": "It's a whole big thing."
      },
      {
        "start": 72.0,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "Other words that contain\nthe root dyn include"
      },
      {
        "start": 74.5,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "dynamite, the powerfully\nexplosive substance,"
      },
      {
        "start": 77.7,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "dynamo, which is literally a machine"
      },
      {
        "start": 79.9,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "that makes electricity,"
      },
      {
        "start": 81.1,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "but also a word for a\nvery energetic person,"
      },
      {
        "start": 83.7,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "and dynasty, which is a powerful\nfamily, like a royal house."
      },
      {
        "start": 88.0,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "We might speak of the Han\ndynasty in Chinese history,"
      },
      {
        "start": 90.6,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "or the Bourbon dynasty in French history."
