f I had to make my bed under duress, that means someone made me\ndo it and I didn't wanna. However, I am acting of my own free will when I tell you that I\nwant to use these words in some sentences. To Ramona, no music was\nmore dynamic than Hyperjazz. Its shifting rhythms, the\nway band members swapped instruments with one another. It thrilled her. It was powerful and constantly changing. It was exciting. Fiona's durable hiking pants were tested to their limits on Daggerback Mountain. How strong? How long lasting were her very expensive ripstop nylon trousers? Only the mountain could know for sure. I hope your love of words remains dynamic and durable, Wordsmiths. I hope it lasts long into the future, changing to meet your needs. I think it just might. Until next time. You can learn anything, David out."
